			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I did the quest approximately 12 times with my monk (I got suckered into being the toolkit grabbing gofer), so yes, you can do it as many times as you can stomach the 12 hour wait.
<br />

<br />
Hand in tools, spawn captain. Kill captain, hand in disk to scout, get reward 1 (robe if memory serves). Hand in robe to get the bracer. Hand in bracer to get the talisman. I may have the order wrong on those, but that's how you get the different rewards. Two hours after having handed in the tools, the scout will despawn. 12 hours later she will respawn. The scout's report you get back is essentially worthless and can be destroyed. Turning it in to the quest giver in Skyshrine will just result in a positive CoV faction hit (along with the appropriate negative hits).
<br />

<br />
Captain can be done with three people, but he is <span style="font-weight: bold">extremely</span> resistant to everything. Booboo'd one day and wound up having to tank him from about 90% health until dead with my monk (warrior forgot to hit defensive, and got unlucky with a string of max hits). We gave up on trying to slow him, although Cloud of Grummus may work.
<br />

<br />
Extremely easy quest for some very nice items (bracers are woowoo material), hardest part of which is the trip across Siren's Grotto.<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">
<br />
Mistomeer C'Dyarnt
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=378575" target="_blank" class="postlink">Arch Convoker</a></span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
